{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1163,"text":"Once there was a star."},{"time":4082,"text":"Like everything else, she was born;"},{"time":6828,"text":"grew to be around 30 times\nthe mass of our sun"},{"time":10633,"text":"and lived for a very long time."},{"time":13475,"text":"Exactly how long,"},{"time":14867,"text":"people cannot really tell."},{"time":17162,"text":"Just like everything in life,"},{"time":18965,"text":"she reached the end\nof her regular star days"},{"time":22438,"text":"when her heart, the core of her life,"},{"time":25039,"text":"exhausted its fuel."},{"time":26905,"text":"But that was no end."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28236,"text":"She transformed into a supernova,\nand in the process"},{"time":31786,"text":"releasing a tremendous amount of energy,"},{"time":34464,"text":"outshining the rest of the galaxy"},{"time":37196,"text":"and emitting, in one second,"},{"time":39554,"text":"the same amount of energy\nour sun will release in 10 days."},{"time":43651,"text":"And she evolved\ninto another role in our galaxy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47783,"text":"Supernova explosions are very extreme."},{"time":50638,"text":"But the ones that emit gamma rays\nare even more extreme."},{"time":55417,"text":"In the process of becoming a supernova,"},{"time":57730,"text":"the interior of the star collapses\nunder its own weight"},{"time":61177,"text":"and it starts rotating ever faster,"},{"time":64089,"text":"like an ice skater when pulling\ntheir arms in close to their body."},{"time":68592,"text":"In that way, it starts rotating very fast\nand it increases, powerfully,"},{"time":73074,"text":"its magnetic field."},{"time":75011,"text":"The matter around the star\nis dragged around,"},{"time":78124,"text":"and some energy from that rotation\nis transferred to that matter"},{"time":81466,"text":"and the magnetic field\nis increased even further."},{"time":85477,"text":"In that way, our star had extra energy\nto outshine the rest of the galaxy"},{"time":91263,"text":"in brightness and gamma ray emission."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94119,"text":"My star, the one in my story,"},{"time":96632,"text":"became what is known as a magnetar."},{"time":99304,"text":"And just for your information,"},{"time":101009,"text":"the magnetic field of a magnetar\nis 1,000 trillion times"},{"time":104914,"text":"the magnetic field of Earth."},{"time":107953,"text":"The most energetic events\never measured by astronomers"},{"time":110633,"text":"carry the name gamma-ray bursts"},{"time":112912,"text":"because we observe them\nas bursts most or explosions,"},{"time":116543,"text":"most strongly measured as gamma-ray light."},{"time":119886,"text":"Our star, like the one in our story\nthat became a magnetar,"},{"time":124115,"text":"is detected as a gamma-ray burst"},{"time":126210,"text":"during the most energetic\nportion of the explosion."},{"time":130167,"text":"Yet, even though gamma-ray bursts\nare the strongest events"},{"time":135492,"text":"ever measured by astronomers,"},{"time":137605,"text":"we cannot see them with our naked eye."},{"time":140266,"text":"We depend, we rely on other methods"},{"time":142618,"text":"in order to study this gamma-ray light."},{"time":145431,"text":"We cannot see them with our naked eye."},{"time":147302,"text":"We can only see\nan itty bitty, tiny portion"},{"time":150396,"text":"of the electromagnetic spectrum\nthat we call visible light."},{"time":154146,"text":"And beyond that, we rely on other methods."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156442,"text":"Yet as astronomers,\nwe study a wider range of light"},{"time":161726,"text":"and we depend on other methods to do that."},{"time":164514,"text":"On the screen, it may look like this."},{"time":167812,"text":"You're seeing a plot."},{"time":169568,"text":"That is a light curve."},{"time":171517,"text":"It's a plot of intensity\nof light over time."},{"time":175090,"text":"It is a gamma-ray light curve."},{"time":178013,"text":"Sighted astronomers\ndepend on this kind of plot"},{"time":181729,"text":"in order to interpret how\nthis light intensity changes over time."},{"time":186933,"text":"On the left, you will be seeing\nthe light intensity without a burst,"},{"time":192473,"text":"and on the right, you will be seeing\nthe light intensity with the burst."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198381,"text":"Early during my career,\nI could also see this kind of plot."},{"time":202562,"text":"But then, I lost my sight."},{"time":205314,"text":"I completely lost my sight\nbecause of extended illness,"},{"time":208490,"text":"and with it, I lost\nthe opportunity to see this plot"},{"time":213208,"text":"and the opportunity to do my physics."},{"time":217672,"text":"It was a very strong transition\nfor me in many ways."},{"time":221295,"text":"And professionally, it left me\nwithout a way to do my science."},{"time":225564,"text":"I longed to access and scrutinize\nthis energetic light"},{"time":230203,"text":"and figure out the astrophysical cause."},{"time":232913,"text":"I wanted to experience\nthe spacious wonder, the excitement,"},{"time":236399,"text":"the joy produced by the detection\nof such a titanic celestial event."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241352,"text":"I thought long and hard about it,"},{"time":244676,"text":"when I suddenly realized\nthat all a light curve is,"},{"time":248385,"text":"is a table of numbers\nconverted into a visual plot."},{"time":252861,"text":"So along with my collaborators,"},{"time":254786,"text":"we worked really hard and we translated\nthe numbers into sound."},{"time":259765,"text":"I achieved access to the data,"},{"time":261793,"text":"and today I'm able to do physics\nat the level of the best astronomer,"},{"time":266830,"text":"using sound."},{"time":268005,"text":"And what people have been able to do,"},{"time":270657,"text":"mainly visually,"},{"time":271834,"text":"for hundreds of years,"},{"time":273202,"text":"now I do it using sound."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275892,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":276953,"text":"Listening to this gamma-ray burst"},{"time":278679,"text":"that you're seeing on the --\n(Applause continues)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":281023,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282198,"text":"Listening to this burst\nthat you're seeing on the screen"},{"time":284930,"text":"brought something to the ear\nbeyond the obvious burst."},{"time":287973,"text":"Now I'm going to play the burst for you."},{"time":289932,"text":"It's not music, it's sound."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293264,"text":"(Digital beeping sounds)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":296539,"text":"This is scientific data\nconverted into sound,"},{"time":299854,"text":"and it's mapped in pitch."},{"time":301112,"text":"The process is called sonification."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306958,"text":"So listening to this\nbrought something to the ear"},{"time":309292,"text":"besides the obvious burst."},{"time":310665,"text":"When I examine the very strong\nlow-frequency regions,"},{"time":315210,"text":"or bass line -- I'm zooming\ninto the bass line now."},{"time":321500,"text":"We noted resonances characteristic\nof electrically charged gasses"},{"time":327043,"text":"like the solar wind."},{"time":328669,"text":"And I want you to hear what I heard."},{"time":331196,"text":"You will hear it as a very fast\ndecrease in volume."},{"time":335001,"text":"And because you're sighted,\nI'm giving you a red line"},{"time":337788,"text":"indicating what intensity of light\nis being converted into sound."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343672,"text":"(Digital hum and whistling sound)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":346110,"text":"The (Whistles) is frogs at home,\ndon't pay attention to that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349428,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":351298,"text":"(Digital hum and whistling sound)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":356549,"text":"I think you heard it, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":359503,"text":"So what we found"},{"time":360804,"text":"is that the bursts last long enough\nin order to support wave resonances,"},{"time":365742,"text":"which are things caused by exchanges\nof energy between particles"},{"time":369983,"text":"that may have been excited,"},{"time":371325,"text":"that depend on the volume."},{"time":373151,"text":"You may remember that I said\nthat the matter around the star"},{"time":376265,"text":"is dragged around?"},{"time":377945,"text":"It transmits power with frequency\nand field distribution"},{"time":381783,"text":"determined by the dimensions."},{"time":384434,"text":"You may remember that we were talking\nabout a super-massive star"},{"time":388408,"text":"that became a very strong\nmagnetic field magnetar."},{"time":392264,"text":"If this is the case, then outflows\nfrom the exploding star"},{"time":396661,"text":"may be associated\nwith this gamma-ray burst."}]},{"cues":[{"time":399168,"text":"What does that mean?"},{"time":400760,"text":"That star formation\nmay be a very important part"},{"time":403751,"text":"of these supernova explosions."},{"time":406047,"text":"Listening to this very gamma-ray burst\nbrought us to the notion"},{"time":410458,"text":"that the use of sound\nas an adjunctive visual display"},{"time":413281,"text":"may also support sighted astronomers"},{"time":415530,"text":"in the search for more\ninformation in the data."},{"time":418562,"text":"Simultaneously, I worked on analyzing\nmeasurements from other telescopes,"},{"time":423904,"text":"and my experiments demonstrated"},{"time":426131,"text":"that when you use sound\nas an adjunctive visual display,"},{"time":430369,"text":"astronomers can find more information"},{"time":433309,"text":"in this now more accessible data set."},{"time":437086,"text":"This ability to transform data into sound"},{"time":440854,"text":"gives astronomy a tremendous\npower of transformation."},{"time":444381,"text":"And the fact that a field\nthat is so visual may be improved"},{"time":448346,"text":"in order to include anyone with interest\nin understanding what lies in the heavens"},{"time":453043,"text":"is a spirit-lifter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455390,"text":"When I lost my sight,"},{"time":457303,"text":"I noticed that I didn't have access"},{"time":459403,"text":"to the same amount\nand quality of information"},{"time":462053,"text":"a sighted astronomer had."},{"time":464220,"text":"It was not until we innovated\nwith the sonification process"},{"time":467724,"text":"that I regained the hope\nto be a productive member of the field"},{"time":471700,"text":"that I had worked so hard to be part of."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475429,"text":"Yet, information access\nis not the only area in astronomy"},{"time":479904,"text":"where this is important."},{"time":482602,"text":"The situation is systemic"},{"time":485150,"text":"and scientific fields are not keeping up."},{"time":488825,"text":"The body is something changeable --"},{"time":491501,"text":"anyone may develop\na disability at any point."},{"time":494890,"text":"Let's think about, for example,"},{"time":497152,"text":"scientists that are already\nat the top of their careers."},{"time":499963,"text":"What happens to them\nif they develop a disability?"},{"time":502827,"text":"Will they feel excommunicated as I did?"},{"time":505839,"text":"Information access\nempowers us to flourish."},{"time":509499,"text":"It gives us equal opportunities\nto display our talents"},{"time":513123,"text":"and choose what we want\nto do with our lives,"},{"time":516010,"text":"based on interest and not based\non potential barriers."},{"time":520294,"text":"When we give people the opportunity\nto succeed without limits,"},{"time":524685,"text":"that will lead to personal fulfillment\nand prospering life."},{"time":529267,"text":"And I think that the use\nof sound in astronomy"},{"time":531724,"text":"is helping us to achieve that\nand to contribute to science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":536119,"text":"While other countries told me\nthat the study of perception techniques"},{"time":540675,"text":"in order to study astronomy data\nis not relevant to astronomy"},{"time":544276,"text":"because there are no blind\nastronomers in the field,"},{"time":547500,"text":"South Africa said, \"We want\npeople with disabilities"},{"time":550928,"text":"to contribute to the field.\""},{"time":552928,"text":"Right now, I'm working"},{"time":554278,"text":"at the South African\nAstronomical Observatory,"},{"time":557034,"text":"at the Office of Astronomy\nfor Development."},{"time":560436,"text":"There, we are working on sonification\ntechniques and analysis methods"},{"time":565201,"text":"to impact the students\nof the Athlone School for the Blind."},{"time":569603,"text":"These students will be learning\nradio astronomy,"},{"time":572113,"text":"and they will be learning\nthe sonification methods"},{"time":575375,"text":"in order to study astronomical events\nlike huge ejections of energy"},{"time":579870,"text":"from the sun, known as\ncoronal mass ejections."},{"time":583194,"text":"What we learn with these students --"},{"time":584977,"text":"these students have multiple disabilities\nand coping strategies"},{"time":588798,"text":"that will be accommodated --"},{"time":590698,"text":"what we learn with these students\nwill directly impact"},{"time":593561,"text":"the way things are being done\nat the professional level."},{"time":596742,"text":"I humbly call this development."},{"time":598825,"text":"And this is happening right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":602350,"text":"I think that science is for everyone."},{"time":606275,"text":"It belongs to the people,"},{"time":607747,"text":"and it has to be available to everyone,"},{"time":610022,"text":"because we are all natural explorers."},{"time":612956,"text":"I think that if we limit people\nwith disabilities"},{"time":618171,"text":"from participating in science,"},{"time":620024,"text":"we'll sever our links with history\nand with society."},{"time":623696,"text":"I dream of a level\nscientific playing field,"},{"time":627166,"text":"where people encourage respect\nand respect each other,"},{"time":632178,"text":"where people exchange strategies\nand discover together."},{"time":635810,"text":"If people with disabilities\nare allowed into the scientific field,"},{"time":640131,"text":"an explosion, a huge titanic burst\nof knowledge will take place,"},{"time":644864,"text":"I am sure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":649251,"text":"(Digital beeping sounds)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":651124,"text":"That is the titanic burst."}]},{"cues":[{"time":654420,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":655595,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":656770,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}